search_results.title: The Mother of Moses
search_results.snippet: Moses's mother was God's providential instrument in preserving his life at a time of a treacherous threat to the emerging nation.

search_results.title: Moses' Mother
search_results.snippet: The speaker talked about the trust Moses' mother had in God in the face of much adversity. ... The speaker ended with this encouragement, “Take heart, mothers!

search_results.title: The Ministry of Moses' Mom
search_results.snippet: Moses' mother was Jochebed, whose husband was Amram. The baby in this story was Moses, of course; Moses' sister was Miriam.
